en_530572_1	Accordingly the nod of the Party was received for the establishment of the new Front on the 05th of this month.
en_530572_2	The Working Committee meeting of the United National Party was held at Temple Trees under the patronage of party leader Prime Minister Ranil Wickremasinghe this morning.
en_530572_3	35 members of the forty Working Committee members that attended the meeting voted in favour of the constitutional draft.
en_530572_4	Only Deputy Leader Sajith Premadasa and Chairman Kabir Hashim as well as Ministers Mangala Samaraweera, Malik Samarawickrema, Ranjith Maddumabandara, Thalatha Athukorale and Ravi Samaraweera and State Ministers Sujeewa Senasinghe, Ajith P. Perera, Eran Wickremaratne, Dilip Wedarachchi and Nalin Bandara opposed the Draft.
en_530572_5	Meanwhile Sujeewa Senasinghe and Ajith P. Perera had behaved in an improper manner against the Alliance.
en_530572_6	The Prime Minister had strictly warned them on this occasion and had informed them to learn how to behave during a meeting.
en_530572_7	Senior Ministers including Naveen Dissanayake and John Amaratunge had continuously pointed out the importance of establishing the Alliance.
en_530572_8	The Prime Minister said that they took action to prepare this Constitution after holding discussions at length with Party leaders involved with the United National Front and with the new Party Leaders.
en_530572_9	General Secretary of the United National Party Minister Akila Viraj Kariyawasam pointed out that the new Alliance will be soon established with the approval of the National Democratic Front with a majority of votes at the Working Committee meeting.
